          "id": "gamma_by_land_use",
          "description": "Brownian-diffusion exponent γ for each Seinfeld land-use category. Closed-canopy classes (Evergreen, Deciduous) have γ≈0.56; open-surface classes (Grass, Desert, Shrubs) have γ≈0.54. Used as Sc^(-γ) in the Brownian diffusion term of quasi-laminar particle resistance.",
